description.plain:
Stokeley Clevon Goulbourne (b. April 18, 1996), better known by the stage name Ski Mask the Slump God (formerly stylized as $ki Mask “The Slump God”), is a rapper hailing from Fort Lauderdale, Florida.

Ski met XXXTENTACION while he was in juvenile jail; the two would eventually form the music collective Very Rare, and later it was rebranded as Members Only.

Ski’s unorthodox delivery and flow, along with his creative use of pop culture references and lyricism over hard creative trap beats set Ski and his crew apart from the rest. Drawing heavy influence from his Jamaican background, he is known for his unique, quick-witted cadence.

During an interview with Office Magazine, Ski stated that his stage name comes from him taking too much Xanax when he was younger.

Ski released his third mixtape, BEWARE THE BOOK OF ELI on May 11, 2018. It featured the likes of Rich the Kid, Ronny J, and production from Murda Beatz. It peaked on the US Billboard 200 at number 50.

Ski released his debut studio album, STOKELEY on November 30, 2018. It featured Juice WRLD, Austin Lam, Lil Baby, and Lil Yachty, as well as production from those such as Ronny J, Murda Beatz, and Kenny Beats. It peaked on the US Billboard 200 at number 6.

Following a hiatus with only a few singles released between 2019 and 2020, Ski released his fourth mixtape, Sin City, on June 25, 2021.

songs.full_title: Catch Me Outside by Ski Mask the Slump God
songs.title: Catch Me Outside

description.plain:
The title of this song is a reference to the very popular “cash me ousside howbow dah” meme that originated on The Dr. Phil Show.

The beat of this track was produced by Timbaland for Missy Elliott’s “She’s a Bitch” back in 1999. It was previewed in a snippet released by Ski back in March called “Cash Me Outside”.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xSX7FwbUwm0

“Catch Me Outside” was cosigned by Missy Elliott herself in a Twitter post on August 1st, 2017.

https://twitter.com/MissyElliott/status/892513151421489152

The success of this track, with credit especially to the music video by Cole Bennett, helped Ski blow up as an artist and get his name out there. Thanks to all of this, he was able to link up with Timbaland, the original producer of this track’s beat, and Ski’s “favorite producer”. They have a collaboration mixtape expected to release before 2018.

songs.title: BabyWipe

description.plain:
The fourth track off of Ski Mask the Slump God’s mixtape YouWillRegret, “BabyWipe” is a track that was teased two months before the mixtape released. However, this was not the earliest song that was dropped on SoundCloud as “Adventure Time” and “EverTookATab?” released four months before this song. This is also the second collaboration between him and producer, CashMoneyAp, the first being “JustLikeMyPiss” which is also a part of YouWillRegret and features up-and-coming Atlanta rapper, Madeintyo.

Throughout the song, Ski raps under the moniker “LilBabyWipe” in order to describe how fresh and clean his flow and lyricism is. Ski was also interviewed by Genius on July 2017 to break down the meaning behind this song.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GSJE9Ja6wC8

description.plain:
“Take A Step Back,” a pivotal track in the distorted trap trend. Notable for its distorted 808s and vocals, staples of X and Ski’s early careers. This is one of the most popular collaborations between the pair.

This song was originally released May 15, 2016 and was later put on Ski’s “You Will Regret” mixtape; released on June 30, 2017.
